{{for|the orchestral conductor|David Charles Abell}}
'''David Abell''' or '''Abel Ebel''' (died c. 1576) was a [[Denmark|Danish]]-[[Germany|German]] [[composer]] and [[organist]]. He worked in the ''Kantoriet'' (the choir and orchestra of the Danish king) of [[Christian III of Denmark|Christian III]].
From 1555 to 1572 he was employed by the Marienkirche in [[Lübeck]], after which he returned to [[Copenhagen]] on [[Frederick II of Denmark and Norway|Frederick II]]'s insistence. In the Kantoriet's records from 1541, there are four choral works by him.
